articles.content:
When setting restrictions on qualifications in accordance with the preceding article, an entity may, based upon the characteristics of the procurement and actual needs, select the requirements according to any or all of the following:
1.the nationality of a supplier or the laws on which a supplier is based for establishment and registration;
2.the nationalities of authorized representative, directors, supervisors, managers, or shareholders holding more than ten percent of the total number of shares or the total amount of capital stock of a supplier;
3.the financial sources and the ratio restriction thereof; and
4.any other requirements as prescribed in laws and regulations or as determined by the responsible entity.
When setting restrictions in accordance with the preceding paragraph, an entity shall also prescribe what kind of certifying documents shall be attached thereof.
